text: Interviewer@Hello, sorry for the wait, my meeting ran over. If you'd like to take a seat we can get started. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@So we received your application and you tick all the boxes, in terms of qualifications. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@We wanted to bring you in to have a chat, talk about the job, and learn a bit about you. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@How does that sound? (((NEW LINE)))
Aye, soonds guid. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Okay. (((NEW LINE)))
Yeah, sounds good. (((NEW LINE)))
Interview@Great. (((NEW LINE)))

Interviewer@CompanyName has a colourful history, as I've no doubt you're aware of! Once a small, humble shoe shop in Glasgow, this company has built an empire in selling shoes around the world. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@I am proud to work here, if you end up working here I hope you do too. (((NEW LINE)))
A howp sae tae! (((NEW LINE)))
I hope so too! (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Are you from Glasgow? (((NEW LINE)))
A stay here, bit a'm fae Kilmaurnock. (((NEW LINE)))
I live here, but I'm from Kilmarnock. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Ha! "Say aye to a killie pie"! (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@It's a good slogan. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Never tried one myself. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@As for the job itself, was there any questions you had? Do you want me to go over the details? (((NEW LINE)))
Aye (((NEW LINE)))
Yeah (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@People think success in business is innovation, market dominance, labour market flexibility, yada yada yada. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@And there's truth there. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@But. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@A successful business is nothing without an army of accountants. Behind the scenes we are the glue that holds it all together. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@What is business if not money management? (((NEW LINE)))
Aw aye, am a hunner percent wae ye. (((NEW LINE)))
Oh yeah, i'm one hundred percent with you. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Good! I'm glad to hear it. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@Can you believe people call this job boring? (((NEW LINE)))
Folk haver. (((NEW LINE)))
People talk nonsense. (((NEW LINE)))
Interviewer@That they do. (((NEW LINE)))
Receptionist@Hi calling about the job. (((NEW LINE)))
Receptionist@You've not go the job, I'm sorry (((NEW LINE)))
Okay... (((NEW LINE)))
Receptionist@You've got the job, I'm sorry (((NEW LINE)))
Yay! (((NEW LINE)))
